  m_Name: Sacroiliac_Joint
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Sacroiliac_Joint
  partName: Sacroiliac Joint
  descriptionChunks:
  - The sacroiliac joint is the articulation between the sacrum and ilium of the
    canine pelvis, forming a strong connection between the spine and hindlimbs. It
    transfers body weight from the vertebral column to the pelvic limbs during standing
    and locomotion.
  - Supported by powerful ligaments and surrounding musculature, it provides stability
    while allowing limited movement for efficient gait. It also absorbs mechanical
    stress during jumping. Injury or instability may cause pain, weakness, reduced
    mobility, and impaired hindlimb locomotor performance.
